# Tube Screamer (TS808/TS9) clipping + tone network — netlist source of truth.
#
# circuitc/netlist.py provides these component values to the discretizer today. The symbolic
# Lcapy MNA front-end (later) will parse this SPICE-style netlist into the same component set.
# Node 0 is ground. Pot wipers split as Rpot1 = Rpot*w, Rpot2 = Rpot*(1-w).
#
# --- drive / clipping feedback network ---
R1     in     a       4700
C1     a      0       0.047u
Rf_d   a      out_d   51k       # series feedback resistor
Rpot_d a      out_d   550k      # drive pot (full value)
Cf     a      out_d   51p       # feedback cap
# Asinh diode/op-amp soft clipper across the feedback path (nonlinear; split out as a
# waveshaper node): Is = 1e-14, nVt = 26m.
#
# --- tone control + recovery stage ---
R220   out_d  t       220
Ctone  t      0       0.22u
Rpot_t t      w       20k       # tone pot (full value)
R1k    w      0       1k
C4     w      out_t   0.22u
R10k   w      out_t   10k
Rf_t   t      out_t   1k
